         <div xml:lang="en" type="translation">
            <ab>Mysthes, son of Ptolemaios(?), the son of -tarchos(?), from the city, (registered) in the quarter of the Tharapeia, to . . . , greetings. I acknowledge that I have sold to you the colt(?) that belongs to me, that has not yet shed its first teeth, dark mouse gray, for forty-eight silver drachmai, just as it is, not subject to rejection. And I have received the price, and you have taken possession of the colt, and I shall give the guarantee.;The sixteenth year of the Emperor Caesar Trajan Hadrian Augustus. Hathyr 30.</ab>
         </div>
